F1 25 TELEMETRY ANALYSIS APP
===========================

OVERVIEW
--------

This project is a desktop telemetry analysis application for F1 25, designed for
post-session (offline) analysis using the official Codemasters UDP Telemetry
Protocol in 2025 format.

The application captures telemetry data broadcast locally by the game via UDP,
parses and normalizes it, stores it in a local database, and provides a highly
configurable visualization interface that allows:

- Displaying multiple telemetry variables simultaneously
- Selecting which variables are shown on each graph
- Showing multiple graphs at the same time
- Overlaying multiple telemetry curves per graph
- Comparing multiple sessions of the same circuit
- Filtering sessions by circuit and date

Although the primary focus is post-analysis, the architecture is explicitly
designed so that live telemetry visualization can be added in the future without
modifying the telemetry core.

This is a personal, desktop-only project intended for engineering practice and
technical demonstration, published on GitHub for reference purposes.

