HIGH-LEVEL ARCHITECTURE
-----------------------

The system is divided into four main layers:

F1 25 Game
   |
   |  UDP (60 Hz)
   v
Telemetry Core (C)
   |
   |  normalized telemetry samples
   v
Backend & Analysis Layer (Python)
   |
   |  structured queries
   v
Visualization Layer (Python / Qt)

Each layer is isolated to minimize coupling and to allow future extensions
without architectural rewrites.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

LANGUAGES AND TECHNOLOGIES
-------------------------

Telemetry Core:
- Language: C
- Responsibilities:
  - UDP socket management
  - Binary packet parsing (Codemasters 2025 format)
  - High-precision timestamping
  - Data validation and sanity checks
  - Emission of normalized telemetry samples

Rationale:
- Predictable performance
- Low latency
- Precise control over memory layout
- Suitable for high-frequency UDP streams

Backend and Analysis:
- Language: Python
- Responsibilities:
  - Session lifecycle management
  - Telemetry ingestion orchestration
  - Derived metrics computation (delta time, averages, etc.)
  - Filtering and comparison logic
  - Database access layer

Rationale:
- Rapid development
- Strong numerical and data-processing ecosystem
- Clear expression of analysis logic

Visualization Layer:
- Language: Python
- Framework: PySide6 (Qt)
- Graph Engine: PyQtGraph
- Responsibilities:
  - Multi-panel graph layouts
  - Interactive plots (zoom, pan, legend toggling)
  - Variable selection per graph
  - Session selection and comparison
  - Enforcement of comparison constraints

Database:
- Engine: SQLite
- Scope: Local-only
- Rationale:
  - Zero configuration
  - Adequate performance for telemetry workloads
  - Easy inspection and versioning

