-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

VISUALIZATION RULES AND CONSTRAINTS
----------------------------------

- Multiple graphs can be displayed simultaneously
- Each graph displays one telemetry variable
- Each graph can contain multiple curves
- Each curve corresponds to a different session or lap
- All curves within a graph must belong to the same circuit
- Cross-circuit comparisons are explicitly forbidden
- Session identity is encoded visually using color and legends

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

EXTENSIBILITY: LIVE TELEMETRY
-----------------------------

Although the system is currently focused on post-session analysis:

- The telemetry core is session-agnostic
- UDP capture is continuous and stateless
- Storage and visualization layers are decoupled

This allows future implementation of:
- Live dashboards
- Real-time telemetry visualization
- Streaming-only modes

without modifying the core UDP ingestion logic.

